Description: Four joining fragments of rim of an Aeolic bucchero pottery dinos; grey slip on exterior; graffito on shoulder. Red paint on inside of rim.
Curator's comments: See also 1888.6-1.634, which is a closely similar piece, if not the same one; epigraphically it would be difficult to unite the two, since the two dedicators would seem to have different ethnics.
